text: The 2020 United States presidential election in South Dakota was held on Tuesday, November 3, 2020, as part of the 2020 United States presidential election. Incumbent President Donald Trump, and his running mate Vice President Mike Pence had won 3 electoral votes in the Electoral College. == References == Category:2020 United States presidential election Category:2020s in South Dakota Category:South Dakota elections
title: 2020 United States presidential election in South Dakota
